@tcbuzor this looks like a mismatch between client and server on whether TLS is enabled (eg: connecting with TLS on a non-TLS port or vice-versa)

the regular client command (`pulsar-client -n 0 -s "TEST" TEST_TOPIC`) will connector to `pulsar://localhost:6650` without TLS.

Use `pulsar-client --url pulsar+ssl://localhost:6651 ... ` to have the client use TLS when connecting.

@sjchicks 

Pull request #3836 will fix the issue of step 1-5.

The reason why step 6 doesn't work is - when a topic is deleted, the schema of the topic isn't deleted. This is kind of by-design, for keeping the history for the schema of a topic. However we can provide a flag at deleting topic to remove schema when deleting a topic. I will create a separate issue for that.
